page: List of Pashtun empires and dynasties
message: /* Disputed Origins */Firishta doesn't call them Pashtun, and modern scholars note it to be mistransliteration for Lawi. Also see my edit summary at the main article.

Sutyarashi moved page [[Talk:Hamid Khan Lodi]] to [[Talk:Shaikh Hamid Lawi]]: "Khan" has been added by the page creator even though none of the sources contain it. This Turko-Mongol title wasn't present in the region during 10th century.

Sutyarashi moved page [[Talk:Hamid Khan Lodi]] to [[Talk:Shaikh Hamid Lawi]]: "Khan" has been added by the page creator even though none of the sources contain it. This Turko-Mongol title wasn't present in the region during 10th century.

Sutyarashi moved page [[Hamid Khan Lodi]] to [[Shaikh Hamid Lawi]]: "Khan" has been added by the page creator even though none of the sources contain it. This Turko-Mongol title wasn't present in the region during 10th century.

Sutyarashi moved page [[Hamid Khan Lodi]] to [[Shaikh Hamid Lawi]]: "Khan" has been added by the page creator even though none of the sources contain it. This Turko-Mongol title wasn't present in the region during 10th century.

Firishta didn't call Shaikh Hamid as Pashtun but simply Lodi, which the source itself notes to be an error. Since he lived 5 centuries later than the dynasty is believed to exist, this statement can't be relied upon especially when the notion is rejected by the modern historians.
